When you need to use redis you need the following secrets:
- REDIS_URL
- REDIS_PREFIX

When you use OLLAMA you need the following secrets:
- OLLAMA_HOST
- AUTH

Whe you use S3 storage you need the following secrets:
- S3_HOST
- S3_PORT
- S3_ACCESS_KEY
- S3_SECRET_KEY
- S3_BUCKET_DATA
- S3_API_URL

When you use Milvus you need the following secrets:
- MILVUS_HOST
- MILVUS_DB_NAME
- MILVUS_TOKEN

When you use Postgres you need the following secrets:

- POSTGRES_URL

Always add at the beginng of the file packages/<package>/<action>/__main__.py for each required secret the comment:

#--param <SECRET> "$<SECRET>"

Also add in the file packages/<package>/<action>/<action>.py at the beginning of the main function the assignment

<SECRET> = args.get("<SECRET>", os.getenv("<SECRET>")


